headline: Down 11% in 1 Month With a 3.7% Yield, Is This High-Yield Dividend Stock Too Cheap to Ignore, and Worth Buying in 2025?
summary: ExxonMobil (NYSE: XOM) and the rest of the energy sector are down big in the past month as oil prices hover around their lowest levels in a year.  Here's why ExxonMobil is well-positioned to substantially grow its earnings and cash flow in the coming years and why it stands out as a compelling dividend stock to buy in 2025.  On Dec. 11, ExxonMobil updated its corporate plan and extended its targets from 2027 out to 2030.
